... a different kind of book ... ... this is a very good read ... this book offers much more than the usual approach of `tell the dog to sit , and reward it with a treat ' ... the author approaches the problem of bad dog behaviour from the owner 's perspective , as well as from the dog 's perspective ... a holistic approach that avoids harsh punishment ... the author tells us that in order to correct a dog , oftentimes we must first as owners correct ourselves , our approach ... our whole attitude ... we are encouraged to try and learn the nature of dogs , their instincts and propensities ... the numerous case studies are also extremely useful ... all in all , a very good book , informative , sensible and effective